        <para> After you log in, more folders are accessible to you.
            When you click on your "Home" folder, note that the path shown in the search panel is not /resources/Home, 
            but "/resources/users/" followed by your full username. </para>
        <para> The "Home" folder is represented in bold typeface. 
            Folders in bold typeface are folders that you have writing access to. You can edit and save records to them.
            If other users allow you to write to their folders, these folders also appear in bold in the Folder View.
        </para>
        <para>
            Folders that are greyed out are read-only folders. 
        </para>
        <para>
            <graphic fileref="images/walk-through.10.png" align="center" valign="middle"/>
        </para>
        <para>If you hover above a shared folder with your insertion point, a tooltip explains who this folder is shared with.</para>
